{"submission_id":"sub_51ecb000dd4d7d4c","run_id":"2026-06-23T16-29-38-258Z_1400822-e67f1169_ingest_meeting-doc-192311","submitted_at":"2026-06-23T16:36:19.032Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:51ecb000dd4d7d4cf1443fa064d6ab6f8bfc9a376aeb21fd95abf620b090e1a0","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_192311","observation_kind":"project","local_observation_id":"project_meeting_doc_192311_fuel_hedging_program","target_record_id":"project_fuel-hedge-program-2022","raw_text":"Fuel Hedging Program: Active Ultra-Low Sulfur Diesel (ULSD) Hedges. MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date.","payload":{"project_name":"Fuel Hedging Program: Active Ultra-Low Sulfur Diesel (ULSD) Hedges","description":"MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_192311","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_192311#p001_b0008","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_192311/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_b0008","text_sha256":"sha256:a33562d071dee23e8a1df1849741c12bbc4ba589837a30e59162b9d7858809e2","text_source":"raw_text"},{"source_id":"meeting_doc_192311","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_192311#p001_b0033","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_192311/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_b0033","text_sha256":"sha256:f9f8a173491325bc61eed9bcff5d0fe8101aeed749a041302f323222ab2db6e4","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_752b4064421b92b6","run_id":"2026-06-23T16-29-38-258Z_1400822-e67f1169_ingest_meeting-doc-192311","submitted_at":"2026-06-23T16:37:46.146Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:752b4064421b92b670afe4d05ab31957169fd0a55557a69a4bdb5be19338eb5e","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_192311","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_192311_hedging_program_description","raw_text":"MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date. The actual percentage hedged could be higher or lower than the 50% target depending on the actual levels of fuel consumption. While the fuel hedging program includes compressed natural gas, there are currently no active hedges.","payload":{"claim_text":"MTA's fuel hedging program mitigates budget risk by dollar cost averaging approximately 50% of projected fuel expenses. The goal of the program is to be 50% hedged for the next 12 months. Monthly hedges are equal to approximately 4% of the projected fuel purchases expected to occur 13-24 months from each hedge execution date. The actual percentage hedged could be higher or lower than the 50% target depending on the actual levels of fuel consumption. While the fuel hedging program includes compressed natural gas, there are currently no active hedges."},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_192311","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_192311#p001_b0033","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_192311/blocks.jsonl","page_number":1,"block_id":"p001_b0033","text_sha256":"sha256:f9f8a173491325bc61eed9bcff5d0fe8101aeed749a041302f323222ab2db6e4","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
